pgTitle: List of Chinook Jargon place names

rows.text: can also mean "milk" but in topographic terms almost invariably "breasts" or "teats"
could be someone who was called "little George", or a child named George
Tenas Lake is a.k.a. Little Lillooet Lake, which is joined to Lillooet Lake by Tenas Narrows since raising of lake level
either a child named Mary, or an adult nicknamed "little Mary"
Tikke Glacier is nearby; tikke is usually ticky or tikegh
could be Carrier, rather than Chinook, but klee in Chinook is from Engl. "glee", usually means happiness or joke
||||tomahnous is usually tamahnous, sometimes tamanass or tamanawass/tamanawaz
when in reference to water, tsee can mean "fresh" or "potable"; this is a semi-arid area with few streams, so that is its probable reference
tum is possibly short for tumwater ("waterfall") rather than tumtum
on divide between Gold, Heber and Salmon Rivers.
also Tyee Ridge Spring Nos. 1-3, 6-8 in situ
